rlm-git-find-in-remotes <regex> [remote-glob]

Search every remote-tracking branch in the current repository for
tracked paths matching an extended regex. Prints one block per branch
that contains at least one matching path, with the branch name (with
the refs/remotes/ prefix stripped) followed by the indented paths.
Symbolic refs such as refs/remotes/origin/HEAD are skipped so each
matching commit is reported once.

Run `git fetch --all` beforehand if you need to include branches that
were recently pushed to a remote.

ARGUMENTS
  regex        Extended regex (grep -E) matched against tracked
               paths. Quote it to protect shell metacharacters.
  remote-glob  Optional refname pattern in for-each-ref form,
               default refs/remotes/. Use refs/remotes/origin/ to
               restrict to a single remote.

EXIT STATUS
  0 if at least one matching path was found, non-zero otherwise.

REQUIRES
  git, grep
